But journalist, lawyer and writer Graziano Pascale
(@[grazianopascale](http://twitter.com/#%21/grazianopascale/status/85722226762072066))
shares a common concern:

> [@MBBATLLISTA](http://twitter.com/MBBATLLISTA) // los extranjeros cada vez
> msas ricos con el hierro uruguayo

[@MBBATLLISTA](http://twitter.com/MBBATLLISTA) // foreigners getting richer
with Uruguayan iron ore

Later he
[tweets](http://twitter.com/#%21/grazianopascale/status/85882223001223168)
[es]:

> Quien controla el hierro controla el Uruguay..Al manejar 3.000 millns de dls
> anuales Aratiri será un estado dentro del estado.

Whoever controls iron ore controls Uruguay..By managning 3,000 million dollars
annually Aratiri will be a state within a state.

Ricardo Berois
(@[rberois](http://twitter.com/#%21/rberois/statuses/85488191880183808))
refers to [President José Mujica](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pepe_Mujica)’s
announcement of a second company – [Gladiator
Resources](http://www.gladiatorresources.com.au/investor-information/project-
overview/) (Ferro Minas S.A. in Uruguay), from Australia – that seeks to
extract iron ore from [Rivera](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rivera):

> Mujica dice que hay otra empresa a parte de Aratirí ! Entonces a
> nacionalizar el hierro si quiere más guita como dijo

Mujica says there is another company apart from Aratirí! Then let’s
nationalize iron ore if he wants more money like he said

Marcelo Bacigalupi
(@[Cr_Bacigalupi](http://twitter.com/#%21/Cr_Bacigalupi/statuses/84964388360032256))
writes:

> EL DEBATE DE ARATIRI ES ESTERIL. HAY QUE PROHIBIR LA MINERIA A CIELO
> ABIERTO. HAY QUE CUIDAR EL 1/2 AMBIENTE. EL CAPITAL ESTA EN LA CABEZA.

The Aratiri debate is sterile. Open pit mining must be banned. The environment
must be protected. Capital is only in our heads.

On YouTube,
[noalamegamineriaUR](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WsyfvFTu2Rw&feature=share)
(no to mining Uruguay) [es] posts a video which informs about the consequences
of a project like Aratirí and also shows marches against the mine:

Uruguayan newspaper _[El
Observador](http://www.elobservador.com.uy/noticia/204406/estudios-de-impacto-
ambiental-sobre-aratiri-estaran-dentro-de-18-meses-/) _[es] reports that
environmental impact studies for Aratiri will be ready in 18 months. Until
then, we can expect the conversation to continue on the streets and on social
networks.

